Pre-Game Insights: Harambee Stars Coach Engin Firat expressed confidence in his squad's ability to compete with Cameroon.
Firat remains optimistic about his team’s chances, but Kenya will have to defy both history and the form book to claim a positive result against the Indomitable Lions.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Cameroon has never lost to Kenya in their eight previous meetings, winning four and drawing the other four.
Cameroon has recorded mixed results, including a 4-1 win over Cape Verde, a 1-1 draw with Angola, and a narrow 1-0 victory against Namibia.
Others: Kenya will first face the Indomitable Lions at the Ahmadou Ahidjo Omnisports Stadium in Yaoundé on Friday, October 11, 2024, before hosting the return leg at Uganda’s Mandela National Stadium three days later.
The Harambee Stars departed Nairobi on Thursday morning and are set to hold a training session at the Omnisports Stadium in Yaoundé in preparation for the crucial clash.
